<section>

<h2>Statement</h2>

<p>
I investigate forms of expression that emerge after the collapse of distinctions
between artwork, author, and viewer.
</p>

<p>
Postmodern art expanded its boundaries by incorporating what was previously non-art.
However, I consider that this process has also obscured the gradient space
between art and everyday life.
</p>

<p>
My practice focuses on this in-between domain,
where meaning, institution, and silence overlap and destabilize each other.
</p>

<p>
I work across painting, installation, text, and archival forms
to construct spaces where boundaries themselves become unstable.
</p>

